the allischalmers corp has agreed to pay the 
federal government 45 million to clean up 13 hazardous waste 
sites in seven states the justice department announced friday 
the payment agreement was filed in new york city where 
allischalmers a milwaukeebased farm equipment manufacturer is 
reorganizing under chapter 11 of the bankruptcy code in us 
bankruptcy court in new york the 45 million payment is subject 
to approval by the federal court 
the agreement was the result of the justice departments program 
to make sure certain environmental cleanup issues are addressed 
when companies reorganize under federal bankruptcy law said 
assistant attorney general roger j marzulla of the land and 
natural resources division 
marzulla said the firm pledged to pay the government regardless 
of other obligations under the reorganization proceedings 
the 45 million will be distributed to the following sites 
maxey flats nuclear disposal site morehead ky 325000 bluff 
road landfill columbia sc 15000 peak oil tampa fla 
25000 conservation chemical co landfill site gary ind 
40000 northside sanitary landfillenvirochem zionsville ind 
30000 schmalz dump site harrison wis 2 million ninth 
avenue dump site gary ind 625000 muskego sanitary landfill 
muskego wis 375000 brookfield sanitary landfill loth 
disposal site brookfield wis 125000 lenz oil lemont ill 
295000 us scrap chicago 625000 interstate transformer 
ellwood pa 10000 and lees lane landfill louisville ky 
10000 
