opposition against the governing social democratic party 
set serenely among woodlands and wheatfields sjobo seems hardly 
the scene for a national confrontation the town of 4000 is laid 
out in neat rows of singlestory homes with welltrimmed gardens 
the immigration department has said the state would pay for 
housing and educating the immigrants 
but magnusson said the problem goes deeper he said the 
government must curb an unchecked flood of immigrants 
magnusson cited police reports that more than half the refugees 
seeking to live in sweden destroy their passports on their way here 
to make it difficult to deport them 
