you dont preserve a forest by putting out all 
fires ecologists observe in defending the let it burn policy 
of the national park service 
the forest will keep changing as plant and animal species kept 
down by periodic natural fires establish themselves and youre 
going to culminate in a few species that can outcompete the 
others said jonathan roughgarden professor of biological 
sciences at stanford university 
