at 85 percent of the minimum wage 
only about 100000 students are now earning the 285 subminimum 
wage according to labor department officials compared with 
515000 students in 1978 kennedy said his proposal would allow 
employers to double the number of students at the subminimum wage 
on their payrolls 
the tactic was aimed at heading off a republican amendment by 
sen orrin hatch of utah to establish an 80 percent training wage 
for newly hired workers for up to 90 days 
hatch indicated that republicans were unwilling to vote friday 
on kennedys student wage putting off the key 
republicandemocratic showdown on the politically volatile minimum 
wage issue until next week eight weeks before the november 
election 
president reagan vice president george bush and sen dan 
quayle rind bushs running mate in the past have all 
conditioned any increase in the minimum wage to a massive expansion 
of the subminimum wage 
bush campaigning in ohio refused again friday to specify how 
big of an increase in the minimum wage he favored 
i dont know how much of an increase he said but repeated 
that any upward adjustment should be coupled with a differential 
for a lower training wage 
quayle silent on the subject in recent days offered an 
amendment while the bill was still in the senate labor committee in 
june to couple a minimum wage increase to 4 an hour over two years 
with a subminimum training wage the amendment was never voted on 
kennedy complained none of the republican training wage 
proposals require employers to provide any training he said the 
real purpose was to give employers a windfall lower wage in 
jobs that have turnover rates of up to 400 percent a year 
who honestly believes that it takes three months for someone 
to learn to mop a floor or change the sheets on a bed kennedy 
said this is a pure and simple wage cut 
he said the republican proposal would provide employers with a 
powerful incentive to throw working families out on the street 
once every 90 days and replace them with a new force of trainees 
this is the hire em and fire em wage maybe we can call it 
the churn em and burn em wage kennedy said the bush push 
will turn americas working people into vagabonds and gypsies 
thrown from job to job every three months can this be what george 
bush means when he talks about a kinder gentler america 
hatch called kennedys counterproposal for an expansion of the 
currently allowed student waivers a not really very effective 
bureaucratic way of doing things 
the purpose of the training wage is not to help fulltime 
students hatch said the purpose is to open the door of 
opportunity for those who have nothing who are undereducated 
unskilled 
hatch cited various studies estimating that increasing the 
minimum wage would cause the loss of between 200000 and 800000 
new jobs over the next three years 
the reason 16 million new jobs 12 million of them at 10 an 
hour or more have been created since 1981 is because we havent 
had an increase in the minimum wage he said 
the federally mandated wage floor has been frozen at 335 since 
january 1981 the longest time in its 50year history without an 
increase meanwhile its purchasing power has dropped 30 percent to 
260 measured in todays dollars 
kennedys bill would raise by 40cent increments each year to 
375 in 1989 415 in 1989 and 455 in 1990 a total of 358 
percent over the three years it also would increase the exemption 
for small businesses from the current threshold of 362000 in 
gross sales to 500000 
according to labor department figures about 67 million workers 
were paid the minimum wage or less in 1986 but the bill also would 
directly benefit 115 million other workers earning between 335 
and 450 
