after challenger beggs resigned and graham remained as acting 
administrator until dr james c fletcher returned in may 1986 from 
private life and reassumed the job of administrator he had held for 
eight years in the 1970s 
where management is weak we will strengthen it he 
promised where engineering or design processes need improving 
we will improve it where our internal communications are poor we 
will see that they get better 
the purge had begun much earlier 
the first to step down after challenger was jesse moore 
assistant nasa administrator for spaceflight who had already been 
named to take over as director of the johnson space center in 
houston truly was summoned from the us navy space command to 
take charge he proclaimed the nasa cando spirit is intact and 
quickly set out a conservative agenda to get back into the 
spaceflight business 
in the nasa structure center directors wield considerable power 
and those directly concerned with shuttle flight were quick to fall 
moore remained at johnson only a few months and left to take an 
illdefined headquarters job that lasted six months richard smith 
left the kennedy space center for a private space firm dr william 
lucas retired from the marshall space flight center which has 
charge of nasa propulsion systems and received the most criticism 
from the rogers commission 
nasa went to the air force for lt gen forrest s mccartney to 
head the kennedy space center at johnson aaron cohen was moved up 
and marshall got j r thompson a veteran space engineer who came 
back to nasa from princetons plasma physics laboratory 
three of the four thiokol officials who overruled their 
engineers and acceded to the challenger launch still are with the 
