rice should be a serious concern to all japanese economic 
planning agency chief eiichi nakao told a cabinet meeting friday 
every cabinet member should take this matter seriously and 
protect domestic rice production 
nakaos remarks were quoted in a statement from the agency 
the agriculture minister and other officials expressed regret at 
a complaint filed with the us trade representatives office 
wednesday by the us rice millers association 
the organization which represents 11000 american rice growers 
demanded that japan allow foreigners to provide 10 percent of its 
annual rice consumption of 10 million tons within four years 
the petition was based on a section of the recently passed 
omnibus trade law which requires the president to retaliate 
against a country deemed protectionist by the us congress the 
trade representatives office has 45 days to decide whether to 
accept the petition before it starts investigations 
the two governments have agreed not to negotiate this matter 
on a bilateral basis agricultural minister takashi sato said at 
a news conference we regret such a complaint was filed in spite 
of the agreement 
the rice millers association filed a similar complaint in 1986 
but it was turned down tokyo has sought arbitration at the general 
agreement on tariffs and trade an international body that governs 
world trade 
selfsufficiency in rice production is a sensitive issue in 
japan where rice remains the staple food rice growers comprise 
nearly 80 percent of all japanese farmers 
