<TEXT>
gold prices tumbled nearly 7 a troy ounce in 
busy trading friday to the lowest point in 18 months hurt by a 
tide of fresh selling and evidence that inflation remains subdued 
the dollar was mixed in slow trading 
republic national bank in new york quoted gold bullion at 
41175 as of 4 pm edt down 675 from its level of late 
thursday and down 1805 from late wednesday a combined loss of 
more than 4 percent gold had not traded that low since march 1987 
bullion brokers said people who had hoarded gold as a hedge 
against inflation were becoming impatient and exasperated because 
the metal had been falling in value relative to some 
interestbearing investments 
these people are disappointed and shocked and adding fuel to 
the fire said steven pepper vice president and bullion dealer 
at republic national bank the more selling that comes in the 
more these people are in a panic 
moreover recent economic statistics in the united states 
suggest inflation will not rise nearly as much has some gold 
holders had expected heightening prospects that the metal could 
test 400 an ounce gold has not been that low since december 1986 
theres been a lot of new selling said michael kramer 
senior gold trader at mtb banking corp a new york metals concern 
the feeling is you might see 400 gold real soon here i think 
next week youll see 400 gold 
lawrence schoen director of midland montagu metals in new york 
said that based on a technical analysis of goldprice trends the 
metal could fall as low as 375 an ounce he predicted more gold 
investors would dump their holdings 
theyve been holding it and holding it and it does nothing 
for you schoen said meanwhile you can earn 8 percent or more 
on a shortterm treasury bill 
some traders said there was evidence of big sell orders 
emanating from the middle east and australia others said the 
soviet union one of the worlds biggest gold producers had 
unloaded a large amount of bullion in the swiss market to raise 
cash 
gold fell in london to 412 from 41775 late thursday in 
zurich to 411 from 41750 and in hong kong to 41984 from 
42345 on the commodity exchange in new york bullion for current 
delivery fell 690 to 41170 
silver fell on the london market to 640 a troy ounce from 
thursdays 644 close on the new york comex silver for current 
delivery fell 141 cents an ounce to 6326 
in foreignexchange trading the dollar varied slightly in value 
reflecting what money brokers called an uncertain outlook for the 
us currency and resilient fear of centralbank intervention to 
keep the dollar stable 
